  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;The proposed hot food takeaway, by reason of its close proximity to nearby schools and in the absence of a commitment to the Council&#x27;s Healthy Catering Commitment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;would contribute to and have an adverse impact upon rising levels of childhood and general obesity in the borough. As such the development is contrary to GG3 (&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;Creating a healthy city) and &lt;/span&gt;E9(Retail, markets and hot food takeaways) of the London Plan (2021) and Policies LP9 (Health and Wellbeing) and LP39 (Over-Concentration Of Uses) of the Hackney Local Plan LP33 (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed extraction system, by virtue of its low level exit below residential windows above, would harm neighbouring amenity in respect of noise and odour and thereby fail to accord with LP2(Development and Amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan LP33 (2021).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
